description: The adviser will seek investment results that replicate as closely as possible the performance of the index. The index utilizes a rules-based methodology developed by the index provider, which is designed to identify exchange-traded stocks of companies that are materially engaged in the global travel industry. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities that comprise the index and generally will invest in all of the securities that comprise the index in proportion to their weightings in the index.
name: ALPS Global Travel Beneficiaries ETF
